Two killed in road accidents in Nurpur.
Nurpur, February 5
Two persons were killed while one sustained serious injuries in two road accidents here on Sunday evening.
Vishal (15), a resident of Amlela village in Jawali, died on the spot while Akshay Kumar, a resident of Talara, sustained injuries when their motorcycle collided head-on with a Volvo. Vishal was riding pillion.
In another accident, a motorcyclist died after being hit by a jeep on the Pathankot-Jalandhar national highway. 
The deceased has been identified as Vikas Kumar (32), a resident of Itava in Uttar Pradesh. 
The police have registered cases and handed over the bodies to the families after a post-mortem examination. 
